# Karta LLM Configuration
# Copy to .env and fill in your credentials.
#
# ============================================================================
# THREE-MODEL ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================================
# Karta separates the LLM it uses for internal work from the LLM it uses for
# the final user-facing answer. This lets you use a cheap/local model for
# the 97% that's internal pipeline work and reserve a premium model for the
# one call whose output reaches the user.
#
#   CORE   (KARTA_CORE_MODEL)   — write / dream / links / rerank / classify
#   ANSWER (KARTA_ANSWER_MODEL) — only the final synthesize() call (optional)
#   JUDGE  (KARTA_JUDGE_MODEL)  — BEAM benchmark harness only, not Karta itself
#
# If you only set the core model, Karta runs in single-model mode (answer
# composition uses the core model too — same as earlier releases).
# ============================================================================

# ─── Option 1: Standard OpenAI ─────────────────────────────
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# KARTA_CORE_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# ─── Option 2: Azure OpenAI ────────────────────────────────
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-key
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=2025-04-01-preview
# AZURE_OPENAI_CHAT_MODEL=gpt-5-mini
# AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-3-small

# ─── Option 3: OpenAI-compatible (Ollama, vLLM, Groq) ──────
# OPENAI_API_BASE wins over AZURE_OPENAI_* when both are set, so you can
# keep an Azure config in .env and flip to Ollama per-bench with env vars.
# OPENAI_API_BASE=http://localhost:11434/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama  # Ollama doesn't require a real key; any value works
# KARTA_CORE_MODEL=gemma4:e4b
# KARTA_EMBEDDING_MODEL=nomic-embed-text
#
# The LanceDB schema auto-detects the embedding dimension by probing the
# provider once at startup, so 768-dim (nomic) and 1536-dim (OpenAI) both work.

# ─── Option 4: Split provider (Ollama chat + Azure embeddings) ──────
# When OPENAI_API_BASE points at a local OpenAI-compatible endpoint AND
# Azure credentials are present, Karta auto-routes embeddings to Azure
# (for higher-quality vector retrieval) while keeping chat on the local
# endpoint. The Azure embedding deployment name comes from
# AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDING_MODEL, NOT KARTA_EMBEDDING_MODEL.

# ─── Optional: dedicated ANSWER model ──────────────────────
# Route only the final synthesize() call to a different LLM while all
# internal Karta work stays on the core model. Resolution order:
#   1. KARTA_ANSWER_BASE_URL (+ KARTA_ANSWER_API_KEY) — explicit endpoint
#   2. AZURE_OPENAI_* creds present → Azure with KARTA_ANSWER_MODEL as deployment
#   3. Fall back to the core model for answering too
# KARTA_ANSWER_MODEL=gpt-5-mini

# ─── Override core / embedding models (any backend) ────────
# Legacy alias KARTA_CHAT_MODEL is still honored if KARTA_CORE_MODEL is unset.
# KARTA_CORE_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# KARTA_EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-3-small

# ─── BEAM benchmark judge (not used by Karta at runtime) ───
# Held fixed for score reproducibility across SUT changes.
# KARTA_JUDGE_MODEL=gpt-5-mini

# ─── Reranker (optional, improves retrieval + abstention) ───
# JINA_API_KEY=jina_...
